ement%2025%20years%20after%20the%20JMM%20bribery%20scandal%20rocked%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20in%20the%20course%20of%20the%20hearing%2C%20said%20it%20will%20examine%20whether%20the%20immunity%20granted%20to%20lawmakers%20from%20prosecution%20for%20taking%20bribes%20to%20make%20a%20speech%20or%20vote%20in%20Parliament%20and%20state%20legislatures%20extends%20to%20them%20even%20if%20criminality%20is%20attached%20to%20their%20actions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20had%20on%20September%2020%2C%202023%2C%20agreed%20to%20reconsider%20its%20judgement%2C%20saying%20it%20was%20an%20important%20issue%20having%20a%20significant%20bearing%20on%20%26quot%3Bmorality%20of%20polity%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%201998%2C%20a%20five-judge%20constitution%20bench%20had%2C%20in%20its%20majority%20verdict%20delivered%20in%20the%20PV%20Narasimha%20Rao%20versus%20CBI%20case%2C%20held%20that%20parliamentarians%20have%20immunity%20against%20criminal%20prosecution%20for%20any%20speech%20made%20and%20the%20vote%20cast%20inside%20the%20House%20under%20Article%20105(2)%20and%20Article%20194(2)%20of%20the%20Constitution.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20issue%20came%20under%20the%20Supreme%20Court's%20lens%20again%20in%202019%2C%20when%20a%20bench%20headed%20by%20then%20chief%20justice%20Ranjan%20Gogoi%20was%20hearing%20an%20appeal%20filed%20by%20Sita%20Soren%2C%20JMM%20MLA%20from%20Jama%20and%20daughter-in-law%20of%20party%20chief%20Shibu%20Soren%2C%20who%20was%20an%20accused%20in%20the%20JMM%20bribery%20scandal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Justice%20Gogoi-led%20bench%20had%20referred%20to%20a%20five-judge%20bench%20the%20crucial%20question%2C%20noting%20it%20had%20%26quot%3Bwide%20ramification%26quot%3B%20and%20was%20of%20%26quot%3Bsubstantial%20public%20importance%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESita%20Soren%20was%20accused%20of%20taking%20bribes%20to%20vote%20for%20a%20particular%20candidate%20in%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha%20election%20in%202012.%20She%20had%20contended%20that%20the%20constitutional%20provision%20granting%20lawmakers%20immunity%20from%20prosecution%2C%20which%20saw%20her%20father-in-law%20being%20let%20off%20the%20hook%20in%20the%20JMM%20bribery%20scandal%2C%20be%20applied%20to%20her.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20had%20moved%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20against%20the%20Jharkhand%20High%20Court%20order%20of%20February%2017%2C%202014%2C%20refusing%20to%20quash%20the%20criminal%20case%20lodged%20against%20her.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20three-judge%20bench%20had%20then%20said%20it%20will%20revisit%20the%20SC%20verdict%20in%20the%20sensational%20JMM%20bribery%20case%20involving%20Shibu%20Soren%2C%20a%20former%20Jharkhand%20chief%20minister%20and%20ex-union%20minister%2C%20and%20four%20other%20party%20MPs%20who%20had%20accepted%20bribes%20to%20vote%20against%20the%20no-confidence%20motion%20threatening%20the%20survival%20of%20the%20P%20V%20Narasimha%20Rao%20government%20in%201993.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Narasimha%20Rao%20government%2C%20which%20was%20in%20a%20minority%2C%20survived%20the%20no-confidence%20vote%20with%20their%20support.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20CBI%20registered%20a%20case%20against%20Soren%20and%20four%20other%20JMM%20Lok%20Sabha%20MPs%20but%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20quashed%20it%20citing%20immunity%20from%20prosecution%20they%20enjoyed%20under%20Article%20105(2)%20of%20the%20Constitution.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709521980000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-02%2Fcq5c2cmg_supreme-court-reuters_625x300_06_February_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fsupreme-court-to-decide-today-if-mps-mlas-have-immunity-in-bribery-cases-5171834%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Supreme%20Court%20is%20scheduled%20to%20pronounce%20its%20verdict%20today