%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20younger%20Sharif's%20position%20is%20daunting.%20Supporters%20of%20his%20jailed%20rival%20Imran%20Khan%20won%20the%20most%20seats%20in%20the%20February%20poll%20and%20Sharif%20only%20regained%20power%20thanks%20to%20a%20shaky%20coalition.%20He%20needs%20to%20renew%20a%20loan%20with%20the%20International%20Monetary%20Fund%20by%20April%20to%20keep%20the%20economy%20afloat%20-%20a%20task%20that's%20likely%20to%20fuel%20public%20unrest.%20And%20he%20must%20placate%20a%20powerful%20military%20that%20once%20exiled%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20the%2072-year-old%20politician%20has%20been%20here%20before.%20When%20he%20first%20came%20to%20power%20in%202022%2C%20his%20predecessor%20Khan%20had%20agreed%20to%20subsidize%20fuel%20prices%20weeks%20before%20he%20was%20ousted%2C%20placating%20a%20population%20squeezed%20by%20Asia's%20fastest-rising%20inflation%2C%20but%20costing%20the%20government%20more%20than%20it%20paid%20to%20run%20the%20entire%20federal%20civil%20administration.%20That%20stalled%20an%20IMF%20bailout%20that%20was%20seen%20as%20essential%20to%20keeping%20the%20economy%20intact.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20time%2C%20Sharif%20was%20informed%20weeks%20before%20taking%20the%20premiership%20that%20he%20needed%20to%20raise%20fuel%20prices%20to%20clinch%20the%20IMF%20deal%20and%20save%20the%20country%20from%20default.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHe%20was%20convinced%20really%20from%20day%20one%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Miftah%20Ismail%2C%20Sharif's%20former%20finance%20minister.%20%26quot%3BThen%20one%20of%20our%20ministers%20convinced%20him%20to%20wait%2015%20days.%20And%20then%20every%20time%20he%20would%20be%20ready%2C%20somebody%20would%20say%2C%20why%20don't%20you%20wait%20three%20more%20days%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20took%20six%20weeks%20for%20Sharif%20to%20persuade%20his%20coalition%20partners%20to%20raise%20prices%2C%20a%20delay%20that%20cost%20Pakistan%20hundreds%20of%20millions%20of%20dollars.%20In%20the%20end%2C%20he%20managed%20to%20secure%20the%20%243%20billion%20loan%20after%20taking%20unpopular%20steps%20such%20as%20removing%20fuel%20subsidies%20and%20raising%20energy%20costs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESharif's%20%26quot%3Bfirst%20stint%20as%20PM%20did%20not%20bring%20him%20brownie%20points%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Majyd%20Aziz%2C%20a%20prominent%20businessman%20in%20Karachi%20who%20has%20met%20him%20many%20times.%20%26quot%3BHe%20had%20minimal%20control%20or%20influence%20over%20the%20coalition%20partners.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20fuel-price%20saga%20highlights%20the%20skills%20Sharif%20is%20likely%20to%20need%20as%20leader%20of%20yet%20another%20potentially%20unpopular%20coalition.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESharif's%20two%20main%20allies%20said%20they%20will%20support%20the%20government%20only%20on%20a%20case-by-case%20basis.%20The%20biggest%20partner%2C%20the%20center-left%20Pakistan%20Peoples%20Party%2C%20led%20by%20election%20rival%20Bilawal%20Bhutto%20Zardari%2C%20declined%20even%20to%20join%20the%20cabinet.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EUnexpected%20Return%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShehbaz's%20return%20to%20power%20wasn't%20even%20expected.%20His%20older%20brother%2C%20three-time%20prime%20minister%20Nawaz%20was%20believed%20to%20be%20the%20party's%20pick%20for%20the%20top%20job%20after%20he%20returned%20from%20four%20years%20in%20exile%20to%20counter%20the%20enduring%20popularity%20of%20Khan.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20failure%20of%20Nawaz's%20party%20to%20win%20a%20majority%20in%20the%20election%20is%20what%20prompted%20him%20to%20hand%20the%20prime%20minister%20role%20to%20his%20younger%20brother%2C%20because%20Shehbaz%20was%20thought%20to%20be%20better%20suited%20to%20running%20a%20large%20coalition%2C%20according%20to%20people%20familiar%20with%20the%20family's%20thinking%2C%20who%20asked%20not%20to%20be%20identified%20as%20the%20information%20is%20private.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat's%20unlikely%20to%20mean%20the%20elder%20brother%20won't%20have%20a%20say%20in%20policy.%20In%20his%20previous%20term%20as%20premier%2C%20Shehbaz%20would%20make%20frequent%20trips%20to%20London%20to%20seek%20advice%20from%20Nawaz.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20then%20there's%20the%20army%2C%20which%20ran%20the%20country%20directly%20from%201999%20to%202008%20and%20remains%20a%20powerful%20force%20in%20its%20politics.%20Shehbaz%20has%20been%20conciliatory%20with%20the%20military%2C%20openly%20praising%20army%20chief%20General%20Asim%20Munir.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20the%20Sharif%20brothers%20hail%20from%20a%20business%20family%20and%20only%20got%20into%20politics%20when%20former%20Prime%20Minister%20Zulfikar%20Ali%20Bhutto%20-%20Bilawal's%20grandfather%20-%20nationalized%20the%20steel%20industry%20in%20the%201970s.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETheir%20pro-business%20pedigree%20remains.%20In%20meetings%20with%20company%20executives%2C%20Shehbaz%20is%20more%20affable%2C%20willing%20to%20listen%2C%20and%20able%20to%20grasp%20economic%20issues%2C%20the%20businessman%20Aziz%20said.%20When%20he%20had%20to%20raise%20pensions%20for%20government%20employees%20in%20his%20first%20stint%20as%20premier%2C%20he%20first%20checked%20if%20there%20was%20fiscal%20space%20to%20do%20so.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EChief%20Minister%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20younger%20Sharif%20also%20served%20for%20more%20than%20a%20decade%20as%20the%20chief%20minister%20of%20Punjab%2C%20Pakistan's%20most%20populous%20province%2C%20where%20he%20gained%20a%20reputation%20for%20being%20a%20demanding%2C%20occasionally%20abrasive%20administrator%20who%20would%20call%20for%20site%20visits%20at%20midnight%20and%20ask%20teams%20for%20a%20%26quot%3B25th%20hour%26quot%3B%20in%20a%20day%20to%20get%20tasks%20accomplished.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHe%20had%20an%20infinite%20capacity%20to%20work%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Sibtain%20Fazal%20Halim%2C%20former%20director%20general%20of%20the%20Lahore%20Development%20Authority%2C%20who%20worked%20with%20Sharif%20on%20infrastructure%20projects%20including%20Lahore's%20first%20metro%20line.%20%26quot%3BHonest%20bureaucrats%20who%20were%20not%20shirkers%2C%20for%20them%20he%20was%20a%20hero.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOfficials%20coined%20the%20term%20%26quot%3BShehbaz%20Speed%26quot%3B%20for%20the%20pace%20of%20his%20projects%2C%20executed%20by%20civil%20servants%20he%20had%20hand-picked%20and%20recruited%20through%20personal%20phone%20calls%20and%20breakfast%20invitations%20at%20his%20Lahore%20residence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Shehbaz%20Sharif%20I%20knew%20had%20a%20lot%20of%20appetite%20for%20fight%20and%20no%20time%20for%20fools%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Umair%20Saif%2C%20caretaker%20federal%20minister%20for%20information%20technology%20and%20telecommunication%2C%20who%20worked%20with%20Sharif%20in%20Punjab.%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20Shehbaz%20was%20less%20adept%20at%20public%20speaking%20and%20relationship-building%2C%20and%20never%20enjoyed%20his%20brother's%20levels%20of%20public%20support%2C%20which%20has%20cost%20him%20politically%2C%20according%20to%20people%20who%20worked%20with%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShehbaz's%20track%20record%20has%20also%20been%20marred%20by%20corruption%20allegations.%20After%20the%20military%20coup%20in%201999%2C%20he%20was%20imprisoned%20and%20then%20deported%20to%20Saudi%20Arabia.%20He%20spent%20seven%20years%20in%20exile.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EChallenges%20Ahead%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENow%20his%20most%20pressing%20task%20may%20again%20rile%20the%20public.%20Pakistan's%20debt%20is%20classified%20as%20borderline%20sustainable%2C%20with%20record-high%20interest%20rates%20and%20low%20growth.%20Inflation%20has%20eased%20but%20remains%20above%2020%25.%20Sharif%20must%20seek%20a%20fresh%20loan%20of%20at%20least%20%246%20billion%20from%20the%20IMF%20under%20terms%20that%20could%20be%20even%20stricter%20than%20before.%20The%20prospect%20of%20raising%20taxes%20is%20likely%20to%20stoke%20more%20unrest%2C%20according%20t