3E%2C%20which%20serves%20an%20eight-year%20term%20and%20is%20imbued%20under%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.constituteproject.org%2Fconstitution%2FIran_1989%5C%22%3EIranian%20constitution%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20monitor%2C%20dismiss%20and%20elect%20the%20supreme%20leader.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20Iranians%20being%20able%20to%20vote%2C%20there%20are%20a%20number%20of%20limitations%20to%20the%20democratic%20process%20in%20Iran.%20Most%20notably%2C%20all%20candidates%20are%20vetted%20by%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fnews.bbc.co.uk%2F1%2Fshared%2Fspl%2Fhi%2Fmiddle_east%2F03%2Firan_power%2Fhtml%2Fguardian_council.stm%5C%22%3EGuardian%20Council%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%93%20an%20unelected%20body%20%E2%80%93%20hence%20removing%20a%20significant%20element%20of%20choice.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOf%20the%2049%2C000%20people%20who%20registered%20to%20run%20for%20parliament%20this%20year%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.shora-gc.ir%2Fen%2Fnews%2F243%2Fover-14000-candidates-approved-for-irans-parliamentary-elections%5C%22%3E14%2C200%20applicants%3C%2Fa%3E%20were%20approved.%20This%20has%20involved%20the%20disqualification%20of%20many%20reformist%20and%20centrist%20conservatives%20and%20has%20left%20mainly%20right-wing%20conservatives%20vying%20for%20posts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20fact%2C%20only%2030%20reformists%20have%20been%20approved%20to%20run%20for%20office%2C%20leaving%20them%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.iranintl.com%2Fen%2F202402204964%5C%22%3Eto%20claim%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20elections%20are%20%E2%80%9Cmeaningless%2C%20non-competitive%2C%20unfair%2C%20and%20ineffective%20in%20the%20administration%20of%20the%20country%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20Assembly%20of%20Experts%2C%20144%20candidates%20have%20been%20approved%20to%20run%20for%20the%2088%20seats.%20But%20the%20centrist%20and%20reformist%20former%20president%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fhassanrouhani%3Flang%3Den%5C%22%3EHassan%20Rouhani%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20has%20been%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thenationalnews.com%2Fmena%2Firan%2F2024%2F01%2F24%2Firans-rouhani-says-he-is-banned-from-running-in-march-election-for-elite-assembly%2F%5C%22%3Ebanned%20from%20seeking%20re-election%3C%2Fa%3E.%20This%20has%20further%20cemented%20the%20Assembly%20of%20Experts%20as%20a%20stronghold%20of%20conservatives%20and%20ultra-conservatives.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20names%20of%20the%20final%20candidates%20were%20also%20released%20very%20late%20%E2%80%93%20just%20two%20weeks%20before%20the%20election.%20This%20has%20allowed%20little%20time%20for%20campaigning%20or%2C%20more%20importantly%2C%20for%20the%20public%20to%20get%20to%20know%20who%20they%20are%20supposed%20to%20be%20voting%20for.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIt%E2%80%99s%20different%20this%20time%20around%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20three%20important%20points%20to%20note%20about%20this%20election.%20First%2C%20this%20is%20the%20first%20election%20since%20the%20death%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amnesty.org%2Fen%2Flatest%2Fnews%2F2023%2F09%2Fwhat-happened-to-mahsa-zhina-amini%2F%5C%22%3EMahsa%20Amini%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Amini%20died%20in%20police%20custody%20in%20September%202022%2C%20at%20the%20age%20of%2026%2C%20after%20being%20arrested%20by%20Iran%E2%80%99s%20morality%20police%20for%20violating%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20strict%20Islamic%20dress%20code.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHer%20death%20led%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.forbes.com%2Fsites%2Fmaggiemcgrath%2F2022%2F12%2F06%2Fmahsa-amini-the-spark-that-ignited-a-women-led-revolution%2F%5C%22%3Ewidespread%20protests%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aljazeera.com%2Fnews%2F2023%2F9%2F16%2Firan-one-year-after-the-death-of-mahsa-amini%5C%22%3Eacross%20Iran%3C%2Fa%3E%20which%20were%20met%20with%20a%20brutal%20crackdown.%20And%20while%20these%20%E2%80%9Cwoman%2C%20life%2C%20freedom%E2%80%9D%20protests%2C%20may%20have%20largely%20died%20down%20after%2018%20months%2C%20they%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Fwomens-activism-in-iran-continues-despite-street-protests-dying-down-in-face-of-state-repression-213514%5C%22%3Econtinue%20via%20online%20activism%20and%20civil%20disobedience%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETherefore%2C%20this%20election%20is%20likely%20to%20see%20some%20response%20from%20these%20events%2C%20with%20women%20and%20young%20people%20wanting%20to%20continue%20the%20protest%20through%20the%20ballot%20box.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESecond%2C%20there%20is%20expected%20to%20be%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fedition.cnn.com%2F2024%2F02%2F28%2Fmiddleeast%2Firan-election-parliament-turnout-low-jihad-vote-mime-intl%2Findex.html%5C%22%3Elow%20turnout%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Voting%20turnout%20has%20been%20on%20the%20decline%20in%20Iranian%20elections%20for%20some%20time%2C%20but%20increasing%20dissatisfaction%20with%20the%20voting%20choice%2C%20combined%20with%20apathy%20and%20frustration%20over%20the%20lack%20of%20change%20in%20the%20country%20means%20that%20many%20voters%20are%20planning%20to%20stay%20away%20from%20the%20ballot%20box.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.etemadonline.com%2F%25D8%25A8%25D8%25AE%25D8%25B4-%25D8%25B3%25DB%258C%25D8%25A7%25D8%25B3%25DB%258C-9%2F652287-%25D9%2587%25D8%25B4%25D8%25AF%25D8%25A7%25D8%25B1-%25D9%2586%25D8%25B8%25D8%25B1%25D8%25B3%25D9%2586%25D8%25AC%25DB%258C-%25D9%2587%25D8%25A7-%25D8%25A7%25D9%2586%25D8%25AA%25D8%25AE%25D8%25A7%25D8%25A8%25D8%25A7%25D8%25AA-%25D9%2585%25D8%25AC%25D9%2584%25D8%25B3-%25D8%25AF%25D9%2588%25D8%25A7%25D8%25B2%25D8%25AF%25D9%2587%25D9%2585%5C%22%3Erecent%20poll%3C%2Fa%3E%20suggested%20that%20national%20turnout%20is%20likely%20to%20be%20at%2035%25%20and%20only%2018%25%20in%20the%20capital%2C%20Tehran.%20By%20comparison%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Firandataportal.syr.edu%2F2020-parliamentary-election%5C%22%3Eturnout%20in%202020%20was%2042.5%25%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%93%20but%20this%20was%20the%20lowest%20it%20had%20been%20since%201979%20and%20was%20during%20a%20global%20pandemic.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESuccession%20question%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20low%20turnout%20could%20be%20problematic%20for%20the%20political%20leadership%2C%20who%20rely%20on%20elections%20to%20provide%20a%20veil%20of%20legitimacy%20over%20their%20regime.%20As%20a%20result%2C%20Iran%E2%80%99s%20supreme%20leader%2C%20Ayatollah%20Ali%20Khamenei%2C%20has%20started%20a%20dual%20pronged%20campaign%20of%20encouraging%20citizens%20to%20vote%20and%20blaming%20the%20west%20if%20they%20don%E2%80%99t.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELast%20month%20he%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fkhamenei_ir%2Fstatus%2F1759192438504120516%5C%22%3Etweeted%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%20%E2%80%9CElections%20are%20the%20main%20pillar%20of%20the%20Islamic%20Republic%2C%20and%20they%20are%20the%20way%20to%20improve%20the%20country.%20For%20those%20who%20are%20seeking%20to%20solve%20the%20problems%2C%20the%20way%20to%20do%20this%20is%20the%20elections.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20attended%20a%20meeting%20with%20people%20from%20the%20East%20Azerbaijan%20province%20and%20used%20the%20opportunity%20to%20emphasise%20that%20it%20was%20the%20intention%20of%20what%20he%20called%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tehrantimes.com%2Fnews%2F495092%2FEnemies-oppose-Iran-elections%5C%22%3E%E2%80%9Carrogant%20powers%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20the%20US%20to%20encourage%20people%20to%20boycott%20the%20elections.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20third%20point%20is%20that%20the%20elections%20are%20likely%20to%20have%20a%20greater%20significance%20for%20the%20future%20of%20Islamic%20Republic%20than%20normal.%20Khamenei%20is%20currently%2084%20years%20old%2C%20so%20the%20election%20of%20the%20next%20supreme%20leader%20is%20likely%20to%20happen%20within%20the%20next%20eight-year%20term%20of%20the%20Assembly%20of%20Experts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20why%20it%20is%20thought%20that%20the%20Guardian%