%E2%80%99t%20stand%20up.%20Her%20legs%20kept%20slipping%20beneath%20her%20and%20she%20was%20unable%20to%20feed%20her%20four%20puppies.%20I%20took%20her%20to%20numerous%20vets%2C%20but%20none%20could%20do%20anything%20about%20the%20injuries%2C%E2%80%9D%20recalls%20Sarah.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20took%20her%20in%20and%20named%20her%20Mehrunnisa%20(Neesa)%2C%20which%20means%20%E2%80%98sun%20among%20women%E2%80%99.%20She%20was%20a%20beautiful%20and%20petite%20dog.%20While%20we%20got%20two%20of%20her%20pups%20adopted%2C%20we%20took%20in%20the%20other%20two.%20Neesa%20was%20paralyzed%20for%20life.%20It%20was%20only%20then%20I%20realised%20that%20she%20needed%20so%20much%20care.%20We%20had%20to%20put%20underpads%20under%20her%20%5Bstomach%5D%20because%20she%20would%20get%20all%20sorts%20of%20sores%20and%20wounds.%20Leaving%20dogs%20like%20Neesa%20on%20cement%20or%20tile%20floors%2C%20they%20develop%20wounds%20and%20start%20bleeding%20from%20their%20sores.%20That%E2%80%99s%20how%20they%20develop%20secondary%20infections%20and%20sometimes%20die%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20Sarah%20was%20part%20of%20a%20WhatsApp%20group%20with%20180%20people%20on%20it%20who%20were%20organising%20daily%20rescues%20from%20all%20over%20the%20city%20and%20sterilising%20strays.%20She%20claims%2C%20%E2%80%9COther%20people%20in%20the%20group%20would%20donate%20here%20and%20there%20for%20the%20cause%20but%20ultimately%20I%20would%20pay%20for%20the%20retrieval%20and%20treatment%20of%20these%20rescues.%20At%20this%20time%2C%20we%20were%20rescuing%20about%20eight%20dogs%20per%20day.%20Imagine%20paying%20for%20the%20boarding%2C%20transport%2C%20and%20treatment%20facilities%20for%20these%20rescued%20dogs.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMoreover%2C%20after%20rescuing%20a%20dog%2C%20what%20does%20one%20do%3F%20%E2%80%9CI%20realised%20that%20I%20couldn%E2%80%99t%20put%20these%20old%2C%20injured%2C%20paraplegic%2C%20and%20disabled%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopen